   224→    /// Processes a single layer by finding host candidates and attempting dispatch.
   225→    ///
   226→    /// The process:
   227→    /// 1. Checks out host candidates from the host cache
   228→    /// 2. Attempts dispatch on each candidate until successful or attempts exhausted
   229→    /// 3. Handles various dispatch errors (resource exhaustion, allocation limits, etc.)
   230→    /// 4. Returns hosts back to the cache after use
